This article is a speech given by Vice President Mike Pence at the American Ireland Fund's 25th Silver Anniversary National Gala. Pence expresses his gratitude for the invitation and shares greetings from President Donald Trump. He highlights the enduring friendship between the United States and Ireland, tracing the history of Irish immigrants in America and their contributions to the country. Pence also discusses Ireland's economic success and America's strong economic partnership with Ireland. He congratulates the people of Northern Ireland on their recent election and praises the progress made in achieving peace and prosperity in the region. Pence concludes by reflecting on his own Irish heritage and the pride he feels in serving the American people.